               <p>JOSIAH HAMMOND. I live in Chancery-lane, and am a <rs id="t18320906-223-viclabel1265" type="occupation">surgeon</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-223-victim1849 t18320906-223-viclabel1265"></join>. On the morning of the 6th of September I was passing through <placeName id="t18320906-223-crimeloc1266">Cursitor-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18320906-223-crimeloc1266" type="placeName" value="Cursitor-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18320906-223-crimeloc1266" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-223-off1263 t18320906-223-crimeloc1266"></join> - my attention was called to the state of my pocket; I felt, and missed my handkerchief - I saw McNamara in front of me; I ran up to him, and the gentleman who had spoken to me produced Dixon; the handkerchief was taken from him by Mr. Alexander - he said he picked it up from the street.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320906-223-person1850">
                  ROBERT 
                  ALEXANDER
               <interp inst="t18320906-223-person1850" type="surname" value="ALEXANDER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-223-person1850" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-223-person1850" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the morning of the 6th of September I was in my shop in Cursitor-street; I saw McNamara raise the skirt of the prosecutor's coat with his right hand - he took the handkerchief out with his left hand, and gave it to Dixon, who put it into his breast; I ran out, took Dixon, and took the handkerchief from him.</p>
               <p>GEORGE GRAY (Police-constable A 42). I took the two prisoners.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>McNamara's Defence. I was walking on the other side of the street, and heard some person call out; I looked, and saw the prosecutor, who said I had stolen his handkerchief, but I was on before him.</p>
               <p>Dixon's Defence. I was going after a situation, saw the handkerchief on the ground, and took it up.</p>
               <p>McNAMARA - <rs id="t18320906-223-verdict1267" type="verdictDescription">
